{"parse":{"title":"Grave candle","pageid":40423826,"revid":754977985,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:1719_-_Salzburg_-_Stiftskirche_St_Peter_-_Flowers_and_grave_candle.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/1719_-_Salzburg_-_Stiftskirche_St_Peter_-_Flowers_and_grave_candle.JPG/220px-1719_-_Salzburg_-_Stiftskirche_St_Peter_-_Flowers_and_grave_candle.JPG\" width=\"220\" height=\"165\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/1719_-_Salzburg_-_Stiftskirche_St_Peter_-_Flowers_and_grave_candle.JPG/330px-1719_-_Salzburg_-_Stiftskirche_St_Peter_-_Flowers_and_grave_candle.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/1719_-_Salzburg_-_Stiftskirche_St_Peter_-_Flowers_and_grave_candle.JPG/440px-1719_-_Salzburg_-_Stiftskirche_St_Peter_-_Flowers_and_grave_candle.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"3648\" data-file-height=\"2736\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:1719_-_Salzburg_-_Stiftskirche_St_Peter_-_Flowers_and_grave_candle.JPG\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Grave candle with flowers</div></div></div>\n<p>A <b>grave candle</b>, <b>grave lantern</b>, <b>death candle</b> or a <b>death lantern</b> is a type of <a href=\"/wiki/Candle\" title=\"Candle\">candle</a> or <a href=\"/wiki/Lantern\" title=\"Lantern\">lantern</a>, which is lit in memory of the dead or to commemorate solemn events. The form of a lantern is commonly used in <a href=\"/wiki/Christianity\" title=\"Christianity\">Christianity</a>, whereas candles are more common in <a href=\"/wiki/Judaism\" title=\"Judaism\">Judaism</a> (where they are known as the <a href=\"/wiki/Yahrzeit_candle\" title=\"Yahrzeit candle\">Yahrzeit candle</a>).\n</p><p>The tradition has been adopted by Christianity from the earlier <a href=\"/wiki/Paganism\" title=\"Paganism\">pagan</a> tradition.<sup id=\"cite_ref-tvp_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-tvp-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The grave lanterns, known as <i>znicz</i>, are a common tradition in <a href=\"/wiki/Poland\" title=\"Poland\">Poland</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-tvp_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-tvp-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Grave_candle&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Candlelight_vigil\" title=\"Candlelight vigil\">Candlelight vigil</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Lychnapsia\" title=\"Lychnapsia\">Lychnapsia</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Votive_candle\" title=\"Votive candle\">Votive candle</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Grave_candle&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-tvp-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-tvp_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-tvp_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://www.tvp.pl/bialystok/aktualnosci/spoleczne/zaduszkowe-tradycje/8984919\">http://www.tvp.pl/bialystok/aktualnosci/spoleczne/zaduszkowe-tradycje/8984919</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-br